<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id80ecd9f0-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id80ecd9f1-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The Communications Act of 1934, referred to in text, is <ref href="/us/act/1934-06-19/ch652">act June 19, 1934, ch. 652</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/48/1064">48 Stat. 1064</ref>, which is classified principally to chapter 5 (§ 151 et seq.) of Title 47, Telecommunications. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see <ref href="/us/usc/t47/s609">section 609 of Title 47</ref> and Tables.</p>
</note>
